/dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its name\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 668}, {\"ngram\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"from\": 679, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"the other side\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"peripherique\\\" ring road\", \"from\": 718, \"to\": 746}, {\"ngram\": \"its poorest and most notorious suburbs\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 830}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The densely populated working-class department north of Paris hosts four of the Games' big venues, the athletes' village and other key Olympic sites.\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 982, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1479529955593348e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The densely populated working-class department\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 879}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' big venues\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 930}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes' village\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"other key Olympic sites\", \"from\": 958, \"to\": 981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' pitch for the Games - which run from July 26 to Aug 11 - leaned hard on regenerating an area that has absorbed wave after wave of immigration and where almost a third of its two million people lives below the poverty line.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1479529955593348e-24, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1032}, {\"ngram\": \"Aug\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"an area\", \"from\": 1076, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"wave\", \"from\": 1102, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"wave\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"immigration\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"where almost a third\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"its two million people\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1183}, {\"ngram\": \"the poverty line\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France not only hopes to use the Olympics to turbo-charge ongoing redevelopment there, but also to recast the image of Seine-Saint-Denis as a crime-ridden collection of ghettos forged during suburban riots which started there in 2005.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1449, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.927457786093397e-11, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"turbo-charge ongoing redevelopment\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1294}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1330}, {\"ngram\": \"a crime-ridden collection\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1380}, {\"ngram\": \"ghettos\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"suburban riots\", \"from\": 1406, \"to\": 1420}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its reputation took a further battering in the world's media after the2022 Champions League final fiasco,where football fans were attacked and robbed on their way into the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.679206138865361e-38, \"text\": \"Champions League\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UEFA_Champions_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1623, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Its reputation\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"a further battering\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1490}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's media\", \"from\": 1494, \"to\": 1511}, {\"ngram\": \"football fans\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1575}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 1604, \"to\": 1613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mohamed Gnabaly is relentlessly upbeat about how the Games could help change Seine-Saint-Denis.\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1718, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine-Saint-Denis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Mohamed Gnabaly\", \"from\": 1641, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1690, \"to\": 1699}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The mayor of Ile-Saint-Denis, the narrow island on the River Seine where part ofthe athletes' village has been built,has seen his little municipality turned upside down by construction works for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1946, 